# Steps to reproduce the problem
1. Create a chrome extension:
  - `manifest.json`:
```json
{
  "name": "getFrameTree bug",
  "version": "0.0.1",
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "background": {
    "service_worker": "background.js",
    "type": "module"
  },
  "action": {
    "default_title": "Find frames"
  },
  "permissions": ["debugger", "tabs", "webNavigation"],
  "host_permissions": ["<all_urls>"]
}
```
  - `background.js`:
```js
function compareSets(fromDebugger, fromWebNavigation) {
  const unique = (urls) => [...new Set(urls)];
  const truncateUrl = (url) => url.length > 64 ? `${url.slice(0, 61)}...` : url;
  const urlToLine = (url) => `  - ${truncateUrl(url)}`;

  const total = fromDebugger.size + fromWebNavigation.size;
  const common = unique([...fromDebugger].filter(url => fromWebNavigation.has(url)));
  const uniqueDebugger = unique([...fromDebugger].filter(url => !fromWebNavigation.has(url)));
  const uniqueWebNavigation = unique([...fromWebNavigation].filter(url => !fromDebugger.has(url)));

  return `
Total URLs: ${total}
  - from debugger: ${fromDebugger.size}
  - from webNavigation: ${fromWebNavigation.size}
${common.length > 0 ? `\nCommon URLs:\n${common.map(urlToLine).join('\n')}` : ''}
${uniqueDebugger.length > 0 ? `\nUnique to debugger:\n${uniqueDebugger.map(urlToLine).join('\n')}` : ''}
${uniqueWebNavigation.length > 0 ? `\nUnique to webNavigation:\n${uniqueWebNavigation.map(urlToLine).join('\n')}` : ''}`;
}

chrome.action.onClicked.addListener(async ({ id: tabId }) => {
  chrome.debugger.attach({ tabId }, "1.3");
  const [{ frameTree }, webNavigationFrames] = await Promise.all([
    chrome.debugger.sendCommand({ tabId }, 'Page.getFrameTree'),
    chrome.webNavigation.getAllFrames({ tabId }),
  ]);
  const allChildFrames = ({ frame, childFrames }) => [frame, ...(childFrames ?? []).flatMap(allChildFrames)];
  const debuggerFrameUrls = new Set(allChildFrames(frameTree).map(f => f.url));
  const webNavigationFrameUrls = new Set(webNavigationFrames.map(f => f.url));
  const url = 'data:text/plain,' + compareSets(debuggerFrameUrls, webNavigationFrameUrls);
  await chrome.tabs.create({ url });W
});
```
2. Load it as a unpacked chrome extension
3. navigate to some site with cross-domain iframes, e.g. https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_iframe.asp
4. Click the extension action
5. It will open a new tab with a text report like this:

```
Total URLs: 11
  - from debugger: 3
  - from webNavigation: 8

Common URLs:
  - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_iframe.ASP
  - about:blank

Unique to debugger:
  - :

Unique to webNavigation:
  - https://gum.criteo.com/syncframe?origin=publishertag&topUrl=w...
  - https://aax-eu.amazon-adsystem.com/s/iu3?cm3ppd=1&d=dtb-pub&c...
  - https://fe27afe8cd2e042d41a7628339e8cff0.safeframe.googlesynd...
  - https://tpc.googlesyndication.com/sodar/sodar2/225/runner.html
  - https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api2/aframe
  - https://aax-eu.amazon-adsystem.com/s/v3/pr?exlist=n-nativo_n-...
```

# Problem Description
chrome.debugger API doesn't provide the full `Page.getFrameTree`. For comparison, I used the `chrome.webNavigation.getAllFrames` API and it can obtain all the page frames. The extension above shows the difference.
Note that cross-domain is not an issue in ay other CDP commands that I am aware of, I only noticed this issue with this specific one.

BTW, I could rely on `chrome.webNavigation` for that but it requires that I add `host_permissions: [<all_urls>]` which I would like to avoid.

# Additional Comments
It's related with chrome.debugger extension API.

# Summary
CDP method Page.getFrameTree with chrome.debugger API doesn't return cross-domain iframes

